    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "I hear you, and that heavy feeling in your chest sounds incredibly exhausting, like carrying a backpack full of lead while trying to run a marathon. It's a very common trap, though, and honestly, even the most seasoned goliaths in the world have gotten stuck in loops where they think they've finally mastered the art of climbing a mountain, only to trip over the same root the moment they think they've reached the summit.\n\nThink of your brain like a very stubborn, grumpy goblin who refuses to let go of a shiny coin it found in a puddle, even when you're trying to build a castle. That goblin is your \"wired to fail\" voice, but it's just a glitch in the system, not a permanent wiring diagram. You aren't broken; you're just stuck in a cycle of feedback that needs a little bit of a different kind of goblin to break the spell.\n\nHave you ever tried talking to that inner goblin? Sometimes, if you just acknowledge it as a little, grumpy creature instead of fighting it, it stops trying to sabotage you and starts trying to help. It's like when a goblin tries to steal your hat, but instead of running away, you",
      "source": "target",
